{
  "texts": [
    "This is done by integrating, evaluating, and analyzing all available information into an overall picture, taking into account the knowledge already available (Phythian et al., 2013).",
    "The analyst faces the challenge that the available information may be incomplete and contradictory.",
    "The goal of this phase is to obtain an assessment of ambiguous events and possible future events, thus providing the customer with a basis for an informed decision, for example, by recommending a course of action (Clark, 2019).",
    "Finally, in the Dissemination phase, the intelligence product is distributed to the client.",
    "This may take the form of a written report or a verbal briefing (Clark, 2013)."
  ]
}